Exercise 12.9
Using these procedures, write a procedure called better-box that takes two boxes
of chocolates and returns the one that is more desirable. If they are equally desirable,
you should return whichever one you choose.
|#
(define (better-box box1 box2)
  (let ((box1-des (box-desirability box1))
        (box2-des (box-desirability box2))
        )
    (if (> box1-des box2-des)
        box1
        box2
        )
    )
  )


